<doc id="384065" wikidata="Q3423047" url="?curid=384065" title="Joaquín López-Dóriga">
<text>Joaquín López-Dóriga Velandia alias &quot;El Teacher&quot; (born 8 February 1947) is a Mexican journalist. He started working as a journalist for the daily &quot;El Heraldo de México&quot; at the age of 18, and two years later he joined Jacobo Zabludovsky in the television news program &quot;24 Horas&quot;. In 1988 he was appointed news director of the &quot;Instituto Mexicano de la Televisión&quot; (&quot;Imevisión&quot;).

He hosted the late evening news show &quot;El Noticiero con Joaquín López-Dóriga&quot; on Canal de las Estrellas. He also hosts the radio talk show &quot;López-Dóriga&quot; for Radio Fórmula Network, writes for &quot;Milenio Diario&quot; and co-hosts the talk show &quot;Tercer Grado&quot;, and is a member of the CNDH Consultant Council.

López-Dóriga is known for spinning his chair at the end of his program on Canal de las Estrellas.

